# Todo List App

A simple web-based todo list application with persistent storage, featuring three main screens: Home, Saved List, and Edit page.

![Todo List App Screenshot](https://via.placeholder.com/800x600.png?text=Todo+List+Screenshot)

## Features

- **Home Screen**
  - Add new tasks
  - Edit existing tasks
  - Delete tasks
  - Navigate to Saved List
- **Saved List Screen**
  - View all saved tasks
  - Delete tasks
  - Return to Home Screen
- **Edit Screen**
  - Modify task text
  - Save changes or cancel edits
- **Data Persistence**
  - Automatically saves tasks to browser's local storage
  - Maintains state between sessions
- **Responsive Design**
  - Works on both desktop and mobile devices

## Installation

1. Clone or download the repository
2. Ensure you have three files in the same directory:
   - `index.html`
   - `style.css`
   - `app.js`
3. No additional dependencies required

## Usage

1. Open in VS Code:
   - Install the "Live Server" extension
   - Right-click `index.html` and select "Open with Live Server"
   - The app will open in your default browser

2. Using the App:
   - **Home Screen** (default view)
     - Add tasks using the input field and "Add Task" button
     - Edit or delete tasks using respective buttons
     - Click "View Saved List" to see all saved tasks
   - **Saved List Screen**
     - View read-only list of all tasks
     - Delete tasks or return to Home Screen
   - **Edit Screen**
     - Modify task text in the input field
     - Save changes or cancel to return to Home Screen

## Technical Details

- **Technologies Used**
  - HTML5
  - CSS3
  - JavaScript (ES6)
  - Browser Local Storage

- **Data Storage**
  - Tasks are stored in `localStorage`
  - Persists between browser sessions
  - Data remains on user's device (no cloud storage)

